3. In `CharacterFactory.java`, aggiungiamo la validazione per l'input del tipo di personaggio:

````java path=Java_Exam_Project/src/main/java/com/exam/project/factory/CharacterFactory.java mode=EDIT
/**
 * Create a character based on type
 */
public Character createCharacter(String type, String name) {
 logger.info("Creating character of type: " + type + " with name: " + name);

 // Validate name
 String validatedName = InputValidator.validateCharacterName(name);
 if (validatedName == null) {
 logger.warning("Character creation failed: invalid name");
 return null;
 }

 // Sanitize and validate type
 String sanitizedType = InputValidator.sanitizeInput(type);
 if (sanitizedType.isEmpty()) {
 logger.warning("Character creation failed: empty type");
 System.out.println("Character type cannot be empty!");
 return null;
 }

 // Convert to lowercase for case-insensitive comparison
 sanitizedType = sanitizedType.toLowerCase();

 // Create character based on type
 if (sanitizedType.equals("warrior")) {
 return new Warrior(validatedName);
 } else if (sanitizedType.equals("mage")) {
 return new Mage(validatedName);
 } else {
 logger.warning("Character creation failed: invalid type: " + sanitizedType);
 System.out.println("Invalid character type!");
 return null;
 }
}
````

4. In `InventoryMenuBuilder.java`, aggiungiamo la validazione per l'input di selezione dell'oggetto:

````java path=Java_Exam_Project/src/main/java/com/exam/project/menu/InventoryMenuBuilder.java mode=EDIT
/**
 * Use item from inventory
 */
private static void useItem(Character character) {
 try {
 Inventory inventory = character.getInventory();
 if (inventory.isEmpty()) {
 System.out.println("Inventario vuoto!");
 return;
 }

 // Display items
 System.out.println("\n=== OGGETTI DISPONIBILI ===");
 List<Item> items = inventory.getItems();
 for (int i = 0; i < items.size(); i++) {
 System.out.println((i + 1) + ". " + items.get(i));
 }

 // Get user choice
 System.out.print("\nScegli oggetto (1-" + items.size() + "): ");
 String input = scanner.nextLine();

 // Validate input
 Integer choice = InputValidator.validateMenuChoice(input, items.size());
 if (choice == null || choice < 1) {
 System.out.println("Scelta non valida!");
 return;
 }

 // Use selected item
 Item selectedItem = items.get(choice - 1);
 logger.info("Using item: " + selectedItem.getName());

 // Use item logic...
 } catch (Exception e) {
 logger.severe("Error using item: " + e.getMessage());
 System.out.println("Errore nell'utilizzo dell'oggetto!");
 }
}
````

5. In `CharacterManagement.java`, aggiungiamo la validazione per l'input del nome del file da eliminare:

````java path=Java_Exam_Project/src/main/java/com/exam/project/io/CharacterManagement.java mode=EDIT
/**
 * Delete save file
 */
public static boolean deleteSave(String filename) {
 logger.info("Attempting to delete save: " + filename);

 if (filename == null || filename.trim().isEmpty()) {
 logger.warning("Delete failed: invalid filename");
 System.out.println("Invalid filename!");
 return false;
 }

 try {
 String safeFilename = InputValidator.sanitizeFilename(filename);
 if (safeFilename.isEmpty()) {
 logger.warning("Delete failed: invalid filename after sanitization");
 System.out.println("Invalid filename!");
 return false;
 }

 File file = new File(SAVE_DIR + "/" + safeFilename + FILE_EXT);

 if (file.exists()) {
 boolean deleted = file.delete();
 if (deleted) {
 logger.info("Save file deleted successfully: " + safeFilename);
 System.out.println("Save deleted!");
 } else {
 logger.warning("Failed to delete save file: " + safeFilename);
 System.out.println("Delete failed!");
 }
 return deleted;
 } else {
 logger.info("Save file not found for deletion: " + safeFilename);
 System.out.println("Save not found!");
 return false;
 }
 } catch (Exception e) {
 logger.severe("Error deleting save file: " + e.getMessage());
 System.out.println("Delete failed!");
 return false;
 }
}
