2. We keep the `Troll` class since it has unique abilities that justify a specialized implementation
3. We added a new monster type (skeleton) using the generic `Monster` class
4. We updated the dungeon factory to create a new dungeon type that uses skeletons
5. We updated the builder to accept the new monster type

This approach demonstrates how to use the `Monster` class effectively while still allowing for specialized monster types when needed. It reduces code duplication and makes better use of the existing class hierarchy.
